9
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:55,479
He really came back to life.

10
00:01:55,479 --> 00:01:56,600
How is that possible?

11
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:58,400
I saw it with my own eyes that day.

12
00:01:58,680 --> 00:01:59,560
His leg was broken.

13
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,640
How could he be working here

14
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,970
like nothing happened?

15
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,680
I heard Her Ladyship went in to see him,

16
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,980
and then he just recovered.

17
00:02:04,980 --> 00:02:05,680
Do you think

18
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:07,560
she used some method to save him?

19
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:10,560
What kind of method
could heal a broken leg

20
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:12,360
and bring him back from the dead?

21
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:14,960
If you ask me,
she must've used some dark arts.

22
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:16,600
Or maybe

23
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,680
he… he's not even human.

24
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:19,880
Not human?

25
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,190
Could he be a monster?

26
00:02:22,320 --> 00:02:23,760
That's possible.

27
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,480
You guys,

28
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:28,260
if you have nothing better to do,

29
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,840
go and turn over the soil

30
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:30,910
in the back garden.

31
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:31,860
-Yes.
-Yes.

32
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:32,360
Yes.

33
00:02:35,079 --> 00:02:35,470
Hurry.

34
00:02:35,470 --> 00:02:36,240
Let's go.

35
00:02:43,050 --> 00:02:44,000
You are...

36
00:02:47,010 --> 00:02:48,470
Sir, when did you get here?

37
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,000
Forgive my rudeness.

38
00:02:50,020 --> 00:02:51,370
I didn't see you.

39
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:58,140
Good, good.

40
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:14,280
I swear, this is the last time.

41
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,640
I'll never use magic

42
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:17,800
carelessly again.

43
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:24,240
You know full well that
altering a mortal's fate with magic

44
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,700
comes with consequences.

45
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,900
Why did you still save that child?

46
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:34,920
Hua Ruyue, we were born immortal.

47
00:03:35,079 --> 00:03:36,280
We live for eternity.

48
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:38,600
Mortals live for just a few decades.

49
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,480
To us, that's just a blink.

50
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,480
They're no different from flowers, birds,

51
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:44,940
fish, ants, and mayflies.

52
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,400
If you see a dying ant on the road,

53
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,060
would you also stop to help it?

54
00:03:57,370 --> 00:03:58,660
I'm not heartless.

55
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,240
I just want you to take care of yourself

56
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,770
before saving anyone else.

57
00:04:04,370 --> 00:04:05,520
Got it.

58
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:10,440
Here.

59
00:04:13,410 --> 00:04:15,730
Next time, I really won't step in.

60
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:19,200
Don't be mad.

61
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:21,000
I just coughed up a little blood.

62
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:23,330
With medicine, I'll be fine in no time.

63
00:04:24,050 --> 00:04:26,720
If I hadn't used a formation
to hide your spiritual energy,

64
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,980
the Heavenly Emissary would've noticed

65
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:31,440
and dragged you off
to the Immortal Prison.

66
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:36,720
I knew it. You're the kindest,
always looking out

67
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:37,880
for the weak.

68
00:04:37,940 --> 00:04:40,140
You wouldn't let someone die like that.

69
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,640
It's not hot anymore.

70
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:42,700
Hurry and drink it.

71
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:56,920
But seriously,

72
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:59,400
